[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6949,
        "end_time": 9244,
        "text": "As we walk through our daily environments,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9244,
        "end_time": 11478,
        "text": "we&#39;re surrounded by exotic creatures"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11478,
        "end_time": 14431,
        "text": "that are too small to see \nwith the naked eye."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 14431,
        "end_time": 18237,
        "text": "We usually imagine these \nmicroscopic organisms, or microbes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 18237,
        "end_time": 22329,
        "text": "as asocial cells that float around\nby themselves."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 22329,
        "end_time": 25470,
        "text": "But in reality, \nmicrobes gather by the millions"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 25470,
        "end_time": 30114,
        "text": "to form vast communities \nknown as biofilms."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 30114,
        "end_time": 33109,
        "text": "Natural biofilms are like \nminiature jungles"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 33109,
        "end_time": 37582,
        "text": "filled with many kinds of microbes\nfrom across the web of life."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 37582,
        "end_time": 40702,
        "text": "Bacteria and archaea mingle with\nother microbes"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 40702,
        "end_time": 43438,
        "text": "like algae, fungi, and protozoa,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 43438,
        "end_time": 48915,
        "text": "forming dense, organized structures\nthat grow on almost any surface."
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 48915,
        "end_time": 50677,
        "text": "When you pad across a river bottom,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 50677,
        "end_time": 52939,
        "text": "touch the rind of an aged cheese,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 52939,
        "end_time": 54483,
        "text": "tend your garden soil,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 54483,
        "end_time": 56255,
        "text": "or brush your teeth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 56255,
        "end_time": 60561,
        "text": "you&#39;re coming into contact with these\ninvisible ecosystems."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 60561,
        "end_time": 63043,
        "text": "To see how biofilms come about,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 63043,
        "end_time": 67190,
        "text": "let&#39;s watch one as it develops\non a submerged river rock."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 67190,
        "end_time": 70799,
        "text": "This type of biofilm might begin\nwith a few bacteria"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 70799,
        "end_time": 73147,
        "text": "swimming through their liquid environment."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 73147,
        "end_time": 78076,
        "text": "The cells use rotating flagella\nto propel towards the surface of the rock,"
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 78076,
        "end_time": 82165,
        "text": "which they attach to with the help\nof sticky appendages."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 82165,
        "end_time": 85703,
        "text": "Then, they start producing an\nextracellular matrix"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 85703,
        "end_time": 89474,
        "text": "that holds them together as they divide\nand reproduce."
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 89474,
        "end_time": 92495,
        "text": "Before long, microcolonies arise,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 92495,
        "end_time": 96939,
        "text": "clusters of cells sheathed in this slimy,\nglue-like material."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 96939,
        "end_time": 100055,
        "text": "Microcolonies grow to become towers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 100055,
        "end_time": 102632,
        "text": "while water channels flow around them,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 102632,
        "end_time": 105207,
        "text": "functioning like a basic \ncirculatory system."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 105207,
        "end_time": 109143,
        "text": "But why do microbes build \nsuch complex communities"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 109143,
        "end_time": 111129,
        "text": "when they could live alone?"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 111129,
        "end_time": 113739,
        "text": "For one thing, microbes \nliving in a biofilm"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 113739,
        "end_time": 117026,
        "text": "are rooted in a relatively \nstable microenvironment"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 117026,
        "end_time": 119793,
        "text": "where they may have access \nto a nutrient source."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 119793,
        "end_time": 122303,
        "text": "There&#39;s also safety in numbers."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 122303,
        "end_time": 125745,
        "text": "Out in the deep, dark wilderness\nof the microbial world,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 125745,
        "end_time": 128644,
        "text": "isolated microbes face serious risks."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 128644,
        "end_time": 130191,
        "text": "Predators want to eat them,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 130191,
        "end_time": 132509,
        "text": "immune systems seek to destroy them,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 132509,
        "end_time": 134697,
        "text": "and there are physical dangers, too,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 134697,
        "end_time": 137110,
        "text": "like running out of water\nand drying up."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 137110,
        "end_time": 140682,
        "text": "However, in a biofilm, \nthe extracellular matrix"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 140682,
        "end_time": 143328,
        "text": "shields microbes from external threats."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 143328,
        "end_time": 147926,
        "text": "Biofilms also enable interactions\nbetween individual cells."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 147926,
        "end_time": 151600,
        "text": "When microbes are packed against \neach other in close proximity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 151600,
        "end_time": 152653,
        "text": "they can communicate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 152653,
        "end_time": 154521,
        "text": "exchange genetic information,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 154521,
        "end_time": 158714,
        "text": "and engage in cooperative\nand competitive social behaviors."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 158714,
        "end_time": 160640,
        "text": "Take the soil in your garden,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 160640,
        "end_time": 163283,
        "text": "home to thousands of bacterial species."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 163283,
        "end_time": 165855,
        "text": "As one species colonizes a plant root,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 165855,
        "end_time": 170647,
        "text": "its individual cells might differentiate\ninto various subpopulations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 170647,
        "end_time": 173350,
        "text": "each carrying out a specific task."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 173350,
        "end_time": 177445,
        "text": "Matrix producers pump out \nthe extracellular goo,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 177445,
        "end_time": 182082,
        "text": "swimmers assemble flagella\nand are free to move about or migrate,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 182082,
        "end_time": 186708,
        "text": "and spore-formers produce dormant,\ntough endospores"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 186708,
        "end_time": 188187,
        "text": "that survive starvation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 188187,
        "end_time": 189607,
        "text": "temperature extremes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 189607,
        "end_time": 192057,
        "text": "and harmful radiation."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 192057,
        "end_time": 194380,
        "text": "This phenomenon is called \ndivision of labor."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 194380,
        "end_time": 199300,
        "text": "Ultimately, it gives rise to \na sophisticated system of cooperation"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 199300,
        "end_time": 203932,
        "text": "that&#39;s somewhat like \na multicellular organism in itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 203932,
        "end_time": 208253,
        "text": "But because biofilms often contain\nmany different microbes"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 208253,
        "end_time": 210365,
        "text": "that aren&#39;t closely related to each other,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 210365,
        "end_time": 213490,
        "text": "interactions can also be competitive."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 213490,
        "end_time": 216908,
        "text": "Bacteria launch vicious attacks \non their competitors"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 216908,
        "end_time": 219775,
        "text": "by secreting chemicals \ninto the environment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 219775,
        "end_time": 225176,
        "text": "or by deploying molecular spears\nto inject nearby cells with toxins"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 225176,
        "end_time": 227981,
        "text": "that literally blow them up."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 227981,
        "end_time": 231201,
        "text": "In the end, competition \nis all about resources."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 231201,
        "end_time": 233354,
        "text": "If one species eliminates another,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 233354,
        "end_time": 237120,
        "text": "it keeps more space and food for itself."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 237120,
        "end_time": 240850,
        "text": "Although this dramatic life cycle\noccurs beyond the limits of our vision,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 240850,
        "end_time": 245743,
        "text": "microbial communities provide humans\nand other species with tangible,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 245743,
        "end_time": 248646,
        "text": "and sometimes even delicious, benefits."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 248646,
        "end_time": 252442,
        "text": "Microbes make up a major fraction\nof the biomass on Earth"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 252442,
        "end_time": 255881,
        "text": "and play a critical role \nwithin the global ecosystem"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 255881,
        "end_time": 258555,
        "text": "that supports all larger organisms,"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 258555,
        "end_time": 259945,
        "text": "including us."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 259945,
        "end_time": 262167,
        "text": "They produce much of the oxygen we breath,"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 262167,
        "end_time": 266765,
        "text": "and are recruited to clean up\nenvironmental pollution, like oil spills,"
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 266765,
        "end_time": 268796,
        "text": "or to treat our waste water."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 268796,
        "end_time": 272814,
        "text": "Not to mention, biofilms are normal\nand flavor enhancing parts"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 272814,
        "end_time": 274945,
        "text": "of many of the foods we enjoy,"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 274945,
        "end_time": 276232,
        "text": "including cheese,"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 276232,
        "end_time": 277286,
        "text": "salami,"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 277286,
        "end_time": 279257,
        "text": "and kombucha."
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 279257,
        "end_time": 281116,
        "text": "So the next time you brush your teeth,"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 281116,
        "end_time": 282798,
        "text": "bite into that cheese rind,"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 282798,
        "end_time": 284442,
        "text": "sift through garden soil,"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 284442,
        "end_time": 286471,
        "text": "or skip a river stone,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 286471,
        "end_time": 288269,
        "text": "look as close as you can."
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 288269,
        "end_time": 291680,
        "text": "Imagine the microbial jungles \nall around you"
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 291680,
        "end_time": 294409,
        "text": "waiting to be discovered and explored."
    }
]